"$:/plugins/Telumire/PLM/readme": {
    "created": "20230420194209916",
    "text": "{{||$:/plugins/Telumire/Commons/templates/readme}}

The setup used on https://plm.tiddlyhost.com to create and distribute plugins. Adds a few features to the excellent [[Gatha|$:/plugins/kookma/gatha]] plugin: 

* View only mode (if you want to see the dev UI, clone or download this wiki)
* Upload to ~GitHub button, using the [[file-uploads|$:/plugins/commons/file-uploads]] plugin
* Easier way to write history notes (see history tab)
* Display draft plugins using the familiar plugin view
* Draft plugins can be drag and dropped into a new wiki from the plugin list. They wont be installed as a plugin that way, you need to export them in packaged json for that (see the export tab)
* [[Readme template|$:/plugins/Telumire/Commons/templates/readme]] :
** [[Macro|$:/plugins/Telumire/Commons/macros/openControlPanelTab]] to locate and navigate to the settings of a plugin in the controlpanel quickly (you might need to scroll a bit)
** FAQ: Create a plugin tiddler with the FAQ suffix, then tiddlers tagged with this title will be listed in the FAQ
** TL;DR: Summarize the important info for your plugin in a plugin tiddler with the TLDR suffix 
** Support message allowing users to show support and encourage the developement of plugins",
    "title": "$:/plugins/Telumire/PLM/readme",
    "tags": "",
    "type": "text/vnd.tiddlywiki",
    "modified": "20230501094519515"
},

